      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. but i'm kinda hesitant about antibiotic ointment because i've had rashes from that stuff before. i've read a lot about how medical grade honey or even just regular organic honey is actually better for deep cuts because it creates a natural barrier and doesn't have those chemicals. honestly, the cut is pretty deep and looks like it's gaping a bit, so do you think if i just pack it with a thick layer of honey and wrap it tight it'll just close up on its own? i really want to avoid the hospital if i can.",
