      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear your concerns regarding time and cost, but it's crucial to consider the potential for long-term damage if a deep cut isn't treated properly. Medical tape can only hold the wound edges together temporarily and does not close the wound as effectively as stitches would. This could lead to improper healing, infection, and scarring. It's better to err on the side of caution and seek professional medical attention as soon as possible. They can provide stitches if necessary, which will promote better healing. I understand it's a difficult decision, but your health is worth the investment.",
      "source": "target",
